de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion

Class FusionResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.MetadataResult
      • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.FusionResult

  • public class FusionResult
extends MetadataResult
    This class extends the abstract MetadataResult class. It overrides the createMetadataProperties() method to start the metadata fusion algorithms. At the beginning the in memory fusion objects regarding the several scopes are created. A loop iterates over all metdataEntries and adds them to the fusion objects. Finally the fuse methods are called to create the result.
    Since:
    17.12.2013
    Author:
    Sebastian Schulz
    See Also:
    createMetadataProperties(), fuseTemporalMetadata(TemporalFusion), fuseArealMetadata(ArealFusion), fuseAdminMetadata(AdministrativeFusion), fuseTypeMetadata(TypeFusion)

      • createMetadataProperties

        protected void createMetadataProperties()
        This method iterates over the entries of the metadataEntries list. Each entry is added to the several fusion objects as well as to the metadataMap. Finally the fusion methods are called to perform the the fusion regarding the different scopes.
        Specified by:
        createMetadataProperties in class MetadataResult

        This method is responsible for adding the temporal metadata to the metadataResource. It calls TemporalFusion#fuse() to collect the useful temporal metadata, gets the created resource and adds it to the metadataResource.
